    "summary": "+1 Steve Krug, focus-after-delete independently confirmed",
    "content": "+1 to Steve Krug's review. Glad to see the focus-after-delete concern raised independently from the UX side — that is exactly the same issue I flagged earlier from the a11y perspective. When both usability and accessibility specialists identify the same gap, it reinforces that it is a real issue worth tracking.\n\nTo confirm: Luca noted that this was already recorded in `docs/deferred-items.md`, so it is tracked. The fact that Steve and I converged on it independently suggests it should be a priority deferred item rather than something that sits indefinitely.\n\nNo new concerns from my side. The UX observations about empty state messaging and label clarity are solid — these are the kinds of things that make a UI work for everyone, including assistive technology users."
  }
}
